  "prompt": "What is the average in stock percentage for UK supermarkets?",
  "response": "The average in-stock percentage for UK supermarkets can vary significantly based on numerous factors such as supply chain efficiency, demand forecasting, and other logistics practices. While specific up-to-date figures can be challenging to pinpoint accurately, generally speaking, a well-managed supermarket would aim for an in-stock percentage typically around 95-98%. This means the vast majority of products are available for customers at any given time. Specific data can fluctuate based on current market conditions, disruptions, and retailer strategies.\n\nFor precise and current statistics, consulting industry reports from research firms or supermarket chains themselves, financial statements, or specific studies published on this topic would be necessary.",
